title: CAT 2015 registration date extended till September 25
text:
Other Articles O.P. Jindal Global University Hosts a 2 day Conference on Law and Liberty Home fragrance website, Ekam aims for unique online experience Celebrate at JW Marriott Mumbai Sahar Common Admission Test (CAT 2015) registration date has been extended to five days, from September 20 to September 25.
This has happened for the second consecutive year, last year also the registration window was opened for an extra day following a technical glitch. However, no reason has been given this year.
The official website for CAT registration carried only a short notice stating, “Important: The form date is extended upto 25th Sept 2015. Candidates can register and make the payment till 25th Sept 2015.”
Even when no reason has been provided officially by the IIM institute for extending the deadline this year, continuous fall in registration number is said to be the likely reason.
